==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catoptrics
<hw>Ca*top"trics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>catoptrique</ets>. See <er>Catropric</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>That part of optics which explains the
properties and phenomena of reflected light, and particularly that which
is reflected from mirrors or polished bodies; -- formerly called
<altname>anacamptics</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catoptromancy</ent>⟦br⟧
